- The integer result is the minimum number of balls needed to clear all the balls from the board.
- If it is impossible to clear all the balls from the board using the balls in your hand, the integer result is -1.
- The string parameter `board` represents the row of balls on the board.
- The string parameter `hand` represents the balls in your hand.
- The characters in `board` and `hand` consist of 'R', 'Y', 'B', 'G', and 'W'.
- The initial row of balls on the board will not have any groups of three or more consecutive balls of the same color.